<hr>
<br>
<strong>REFERENCE LIST ENTRY</strong>
<br>
<br>
Add a reference list at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body of your writing.
<br>
<br>
Different works by the same author(s) are listed in chronological (date) order.
<br>
If several works have the same date as well as the same author, works are distinguished by suffixes 
a, b, c, etc. These are allocated in the reference list where they are ordered alphabetically by title.
<br>
References with the same first author and a different second or third author are listed alphabetically.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	Author(s). (Year of publication [suffix]). <em>Title of book</em>. Place of publication: Publisher.
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Example</strong>
<br>
<blockquote>
	<div class="ref-hang-indent">
		<span class="hover" title="Author">Smith, A.</span> 
		(<span class="hover" title="Year of publication">2050</span>). 
		<em><span class="hover" title="Title of book">Exploring nanoscale science</span></em>. 
		<span class="hover" title="Place of publication">San Francisco, CA</span>: 
		<span class="hover" title="Publisher">Beck</span>.
	</div>
	<div class="ref-hang-indent">
		Smith, A. (2056). <em>Amid fifty thousand flaming devils</em>. Baghdad, Iraq: Etoile Press.
	</div>
	<div class="ref-hang-indent">
		Smith, A., &amp; Brown, B. W. (2056a)&hellip;
	</div>
	<div class="ref-hang-indent">
		Smith, A., &amp; Brown, B. W. (2056b)&hellip;
	</div>
	<div class="ref-hang-indent">
		Smith, A., &amp; Chan, C. (2056)&hellip;
	</div>
</blockquote>
