<strong>IN&#45;TEXT CITATION</strong>
<br>
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	Smith and Brown (2056a) indicated that&hellip;
	<br>
	Alternatively: A recent study (Smith &amp; Brown, 2056a) indicated that&hellip;
</blockquote>
<br>
If two or more sources are being cited for the same ideas or information, the author&#8217;s name(s) 
should appear only once and the works are identified by the publication dates (and suffix).
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	Studies indicate that&hellip; (Smith &amp; Brown, 2056a, 2056b).
</blockquote>
<br>
If you are making a direct quotation, use quotation marks and include page numbers.
<br>
<blockquote class="in-text-citation">
	Smith and Brown (2056a) observe that &#34;the Higgs Boson particle still remains illusive&#34; 
	(p. 34).
	<br>
	Alternatively: Therefore, &#34;the Higgs Boson particle still remains illusive&#34; 
	(Smith &amp; Brown, 2056a, p. 34).
</blockquote>
